    dc:title "Nematodes of the order Dorylaimida from Andalucía Oriental, Spain. The genus Enchodelus Thorne, 1939. 2. Description of three known species with rounded tail and long odontostyle" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8111862>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8111864> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8111862>
    dc:description "Fig. 3. SEM micrographs. A-C: Enchodelus groenlandicus (Ditlevsen, 1927) Thorne, 1939, anterior end. A: Semi en face view; B: Lateral view; C: En face view. D-F: Enchodelus macrodorus (de Man, 1880) Thorne, 1939, anterior end. D: Semi en face view; E: Lateral view; F: En face view. G-I: Enchodelus saxifragae Popovici, 1995, anterior end. G: Semi en face view; H: Lateral view; I: En face view. J-L: Vulval region, J: Enchodelus groenlandicus; K: Enchodelus macrodorus; L: Enchodelus saxifragae. (Scale bars: A, B, E, G, H, J-L = 20 µm; C, D, F, I = 10 µm.)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8111862/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8111864>
    dc:description "Fig. 4. Enchodelus macrodorus (de Man, 1880) Thorne, 1939 (female). A: Variability of anterior region; B: Neck showing dorsal gland nucleus (large arrow) and one of subventral gland nuclei (small arrow); C: Anterior genital branch showing sphincter between uterus and oviduct (arrow); D: Detail of uterus-oviduct junction, displaying sphincter (arrow) and weak development of uterus; E: Vulval region; F; Entire body; G: Variability of tail. (Scale bars: A, D, E, G = 20 µm; B = 100 µm; C = 50 µm; F = 250 µm.)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8111864/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

